      <para>
        Memory hot plugging on &productname; allows administrators to add or remove physical or virtual RAM while the system is running. By configuring motherboard firmware and kernel boot parameters, users can dynamically scale infrastructure or replace failing modules without system downtime or risking kernel panics.
      </para>
